main event: An unidentified bright object was observed by a civilian in Osceola, Wisconsin on October 5, 1966, for about 20 minutes.
interesting points: The object was observed moving westward and appeared bright and large,The observer described it as passing between her and the trees,The sighting lasted about 20 minutes and the object was seen both stationary and moving,No physical evidence or photographs were obtained during the sighting,Some military personnel in the area claimed to have seen a similar bright object that night.
